definition: ancient bronze wine holder with 3 legs and loop handle/nobility
order of feudal nobility, namely: Duke 公[gong1], Marquis 侯[hou2], Count 伯[bo2], Viscount 子[zi3], Baron 男[nan2]

sentences.english: A noblewoman holding the rank of viscount in her own right.

sentences.english: Our buying rate for notes is 345 yen for 100 dollars.
sentences.chinese: 爵美元的现金买入价是三百四十五日元。

sentences.english: A key component of the Center is the St. Ignatius Chapel.
sentences.chinese: 该中心的一个重要组成部分就是圣依纳爵教堂。

sentences.english: He stretched forth his hand to make a libation, and offered of the blood of the grape.
sentences.chinese: 就伸手放在尊祭的爵上，然后取爵，尊祭葡萄酒。

sentences.english: I do not know, but I think that is a monkey, Sir Gavin .
sentences.chinese: 我不知道，但我想那是个猴子，加文娚爵。

sentences.english: Later, her own divorce from Lord Snowdon heralded a cavalcade of failed royal marriages.
sentences.chinese: 爵离婚，掀开了王室一桩桩失败婚姻的序幕。
